foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: The Department of Education has a centralized process for processing appeals. The OM-RIMS staff process all appeals.

foia:OtherDenialReason.foia:OtherDenialReasonDescriptionText: Actions completed, docs can now be released in full. Appeal Moot.

foia:ExpeditedProcessingSection.foia:FootnoteText: The Department of Education has a centralized processing program for all Headquarters programs.
The OM-RIMS Office adjudicates requests for expedited processing and issues determination letters.

foia:FeeWaiverSection.foia:FootnoteText: The Department of Education has a centralized processing program for all Headquarters programs. The OM-RIMS Office adjudicates requests for expedited processing and issues determination letters.

foia:PersonnelAndCostSection.foia:FootnoteText: The Processing Costs for OM-RIMS included $86,588 costs for the electronic processing program that is used Department-wide.

foia:FeesCollectedSection.foia:FootnoteText: The Department of Education has a centralized fee collection process. The fees collected are reflected for each program and OCR Field Office that generated the fee.

foia:BacklogSection.foia:FootnoteText: Backlogged requests are requests (or appeals) pending greater than 20 days, the number of which may not be the same as the number of requests (or appeals) carried over from the previous year.

foia:BackloggedAppealComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: Backlogged appeals are appeals pending greater than 20 days, the number of which may not be the same as the number of appeals carried over from the previous year.
